-- U.S. Stock-Index Futures Retreat on Earnings; GE, Google Shares Decline
-- Elizabeth Stanton
-- 2010-07-16T12:05:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/u-s-stock-index-futures-retreat-on-earnings-ge-google-shares-decline.html

          
          
             U.S. stock futures erased earlier
gains as General Electric Co., Citigroup Inc., Bank of America
Corp. and Google Inc. declined after reporting second-quarter
results, offsetting Goldman Sachs Group Inc.’s settlement of a
federal government fraud lawsuit.  
 Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index expiring in
September lost 0.1 percent to 1,089.2 at 8:05 a.m. in New York.
Dow Jones Industrial Average futures retreated 21 points, or 0.2
percent, to 10,271.   
          
          


  


        